        public TalonSRX​(int enablePort,
                int forwardPort,
                int backwardPort)
        Constructs a new Talon using a digital H-Bridge motor.
        Parameters:
        enablePort - the GPIO port used to enable the channel (the magnitude of the speed)
        forwardPort - the GPIO port which is used to change the sign of the forward direction
        backwardPort - the GPIO port which is used to change the sign of the backward direction

        public void set​(TalonSRX.ControlMode mode,

                TalonSRX.DemandType dt,

        Sets the Talon to a given output.
        Parameters:
        mode - the mode of control to be performed on the Talon (including % output, velocity, and position)
        magnitude - the magnitude of the value to be set
        dt - the demand type to be added to the output (like a feed forward or an auxiliary sensor value)
        demandValue - the magnitude of the demand type
